aVPresident Donald Trump announced in a Tuesday morning tweet that he will hold a briefing on the opioid crisis later in the day.\u000a\u000aI will be holding a major briefing on the Opioid crisis, a major problem for our country, today at 3:00 P.M. in Bedminster, N.J. \u2014 Donald J. Trump (@realDonaldTrump) August 8, 2017\u000a\u000aThe announcement was part of a series of tweets the president sent early on Tuesday for the second straight day of his vacation. However, unlike his Twitter rampage on Monday which included repeated insults against individuals and the "fake media," as well as attempts to defend himself against criticism, Trump's latest messages were focused on issues.\u000a\u000aThe president started Tuesday by tweeting several items from "Fox & Friends" that touched on national and international events, including an update on the opioid crisis.\u000a\u000aU.S. spy satellites detect North Korea moving anti-ship cruise missiles to patrol boat https://t.co/BPFXsLffgy \u2014 FOX & friends (@foxandfriends) August 8, 2017\u000a\u000aAnthem announces it will withdraw from ObamaCare Exchange in Nevada pic.twitter.com/d0CxeHQKwz \u2014 FOX & friends (@foxandfriends) August 8, 2017\u000a\u000aOPIOID CRISIS: Worse than we thought, with a new study showing overdose deaths were under reported pic.twitter.com/27kLJKRXsL \u2014 FOX & friends (@foxandfriends) August 8, 2017\u000a\u000aThe president then commented on a few of the issues discussed on "Fox & Friends," including his announcement of the opioid briefing, as well as a tweet on the situation in North Korea.\u000a\u000aAfter many years of failure, countries are coming together to finally address the dangers posed by North Korea. We must be tough & decisive! \u2014 Donald J. Trump (@realDonaldTrump) August 8, 2017\u000a\u000aTrump is vacationing in New Jersey, where Gov. Chris Christie is chairman of the president's opioid commission.
