aVJust 35 percent of Americans are confident in President Donald Trump's ability to handle the North Korea nuclear situation, while 61 percent say they are uneasy, a new CBS News poll reveals.\u000a\u000aHere are the results by party affiliation:\u000a\u000aRepublicans:\u000a\u000aConfident: 76 percent.\u000a\u000aUneasy: 22 percent.\u000a\u000aDemocrats:\u000a\u000aConfident: 10 percent.\u000a\u000aUneasy: 87 percent.\u000a\u000aIndependents:\u000a\u000aConfident: 31 percent.\u000a\u000aUneasy: 64 percent.\u000a\u000aHere are the highlights from the rest of the poll:\u000a\u000aSeventy-two percent are uneasy about a possible conflict with North Korea, while 26 percent are confident things will be resolved.\u000a\u000aSixty percent said North Korea's development of weapons is a threat that can be contained, 29 percent say it requires military action now and 7 percent say it is not a threat at all.\u000a\u000aThe poll, conducted Aug. 3-6, surveyed 1,111 people. It has a margin of error of plus or minus 4 percentage points.
