aVSixty-nine percent of Americans say the economy is in good condition compared to just 30 percent who say it is bad, according to a new CBS News poll.\u000a\u000aHere are the highlights from the survey:\u000a\u000aPresident Donald Trump's handling of the economy:\u000a\u000aApprove: 46 percent.\u000a\u000aDisapprove: 45 percent.\u000a\u000aTrade:\u000a\u000aApprove: 38 percent.\u000a\u000aDisapprove: 45 percent.\u000a\u000aImmigration:\u000a\u000aApprove: 37 percent.\u000a\u000aDisapprove: 57 percent.\u000a\u000aHealthcare:\u000a\u000aApprove: 32 percent.\u000a\u000aDisapprove: 59 percent.\u000a\u000aTrump's job performance:\u000a\u000aApprove: 36 percent.\u000a\u000aDisapprove: 58 percent.\u000a\u000aThe poll, conducted Aug. 3-6, sampled 1,111 adults nationwide. It has a margin of error of plus or minus 4 percentage points.
