aVSave My Care, a group that supports Obamacare, unveiled a digital ad campaign against congressional Republicans who voted to repeal the healthcare law.\u000a\u000aThe progressive group\u2019s ads target two senators who may lose their seat in the midterm elections, Sens. Jeff Flake, R-Ariz., and Dean Heller, R-Nev., as well as Shelley Moore Capito, R-W.Va., who is not up for re-election in 2018.\u000a\u000aIn the lower chamber, the ads go after GOP Reps. John Faso of New York, Tom MacArthur of New Jersey, Dave Brat of Virginia, Peter Roskam of Illinois, Pete Sessions of Texas, and Darrell Issa and David Valadao of California.\u000a\u000aThe videos accuse the legislators of breaking their "promise" to their state, having "voted for the healthcare repeal bill that would\u2019ve taken coverage away" from millions, according to The Hill.\u000a\u000a"Poll after poll has shown abysmal support for repeal among the American people, with the latest Kaiser tracking poll showing seven in ten Americans (71 percent) want Republicans in Congress to work with Democrats to make improvements to the ACA, not repeal the law," the group said, according to The Washington Examiner.
